&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;A quick snapshot&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;strong&gt;…&lt;br&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;The Renewals Manager is responsible for owning the end-to-end renewal lifecycle for a defined portfolio of customers across the Americas. This role is critical to protecting and growing Conga’s recurring revenue base by driving timely, high-quality renewals that align with both customer objectives and business goals.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Sitting at the intersection of Sales and Customer Success, the Renewal Manager proactively manages renewal risk, negotiates contract terms, and partners cross-functionally to deliver a seamless renewal experience. Success in this role is measured primarily by Gross Renewal Rate with Price Increase (GRRw/PI), Net Revenue Retention (NRR), and on-time renewal rate.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;br&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Why it’s a big deal…&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&amp;nbsp;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Renewal Ownership &amp;amp; Pipeline Management&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Own a portfolio of renewal accounts across the Americas, managing the full renewal cycle from initial outreach through signed contract.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Engage customers proactively 90–180 days prior to renewal to assess health, surface risks, and align on terms.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Maintain an accurate renewal forecast in Salesforce and Clari. Provide weekly pipeline updates to leadership.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Prioritize accounts by ARR at risk, customer health score, and days to renewal.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Negotiation &amp;amp; Contracting&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Lead renewal negotiations with a focus on value realization, contract simplification, and mutual outcomes.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Structure renewal proposals that include multi-year options, price escalation clauses, and volume-based discounts.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Partner with Legal, Deal Desk, and Finance to resolve non-standard contract terms and approvals.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ensure all renewal documentation is executed accurately and on time.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Risk Mitigation &amp;amp; Churn Prevention&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Identify at-risk accounts early and develop mitigation strategies in partnership with Customer Success, Sales, Legal, Finance, and Product.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Escalate high-risk accounts appropriately, engaging executive sponsors and product teams as needed.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Track and report on churn drivers, renewal blockers, and win/loss trends.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
